# SpaMe hard invariants

This repo is authored against **Opus 4.7**. Set it as the default model in every Cursor mode. Plan mode is the default Agent mode; switch to Agent only after a plan is confirmed.

**Never relax these 9 invariants** (source: [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md), [docs/vision/SpaMe-vision.md](../../docs/vision/SpaMe-vision.md)):

1. Conversational AI agent **never writes to the DB directly** — only calls Zod-validated server actions.
2. Conversational AI agent **does not pick therapists or rooms** — the server-side auto-assignment engine does, post-payment.
3. **No therapist is notified until the manager publishes.** Auto-assignment, edits, approval are all silent.
4. **Capacity (therapist + room) is held at engine-selection time.** `auto_suggested` / `auto_assigned` / `published` / `therapist_confirmed` block; `pending_payment` and `cancelled` do not.
5. **Every AI-drafted outbound reply is approved by a receptionist OR super admin.** No auto-send in V1.
6. **Payment webhook is the source of truth** for payment success.
7. **Therapist identity AND room identity are anonymous** on every customer-facing surface.
8. **Three booking paths (web / WhatsApp / receptionist), one source of truth** — same DB, same overlap constraints, same payment pipeline, same assignment lifecycle.
9. **Customer + therapist surfaces render in full HE/EN/RU with no fallbacks.** Admin + reception may fall back to EN.

## Working rhythm

- **One feature = one chat.** At ~40 turns or when compaction kicks in, fill [docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md](../../docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md), open a fresh chat, paste the handoff.
- **Plan mode for migrations, schema changes, multi-file refactors, ambiguous asks.** Agent mode only for implementation after a confirmed plan.
- **Before commit:** walk [docs/DOC-SYNC.md](../../docs/DOC-SYNC.md); run `npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm run test && npm run build`.
- **Single source of truth for dangerous commands:** `.cursor/hooks/guard-shell.sh` (not mirrored in Cursor Settings).

